I absolutely love this. It’s a surprising ray of hope in a hall of eldritch horrors and endless cycles of futility that even some of the sillier Skips present in their undertones. The Foundation has cracked the code of heaven, they can forcibly direct souls into it with some negotiation of other extra-dimensional entities and some good old-fashioned hard work. It’s an interesting look into the moral ambiguity that the Foundation employs in its mission, too. It’ll be interesting to imagine how they’d deploy this without lifting the veil/breaking the masquerade, without homogenizing the planet beyond the concept of protection, and without forcing it upon people who wish to abstain from an afterlife altogether.





